threats.tagLine: Anthropogenic pressures on birds, habitats they rely on, and/or an entire ecosystem
threats.title: Over 50% of North America’s vast native grasslands that originally covered over 300 million acres have been lost due to:
threats.description:
• Conversion to row crop agriculture
  • Woody shrub encroachment due to fire supression and prairie dog declines
  • Urbanization and energy development
  • Unsustainable livestock management practices
  • Desertification
  • Short-term and localized landowner incentive programs
  • Failed policy approaches

actions.tagLine: Conservation interventions by Audubon field staff and partners as classifed by the Open Standards for the Practice of Conservation
actions.title: Program Goals:
actions.description:
• Leverage Audubon’s brand to drive consumer interest in ecologically sustainable beef production
  • Develop market-based conservation solutions that help land managers increase their profitability while adopting bird-friendly land management practices.
  • Audubon’s policy team, working with a coalition of stakeholders, will engage in reauthorization of the U.S. Farm Bill to promote policies and increase funding available to landowners for conservation

objectives.description: Continue working with local ranchers to promote sustainable ranching through market-based incentives to conserve 1,000,000 acres of critical grassland bird habitat by 2020
Protect and restore 10 million acres of ecologically intact grassland habitats throughout North America by 2023

chart.value_type: Number of Ranch Acres Enrolled in the Conservation Ranching Program

response.tagLine: Quantifying the effectiveness of our conservation actions using scientifically-sound metrics
response.title: Grassland birds have suffered sharp declines over the past half century
response.description: • We will measure the impact of the Conservation Ranching program with a novel index of ecological resilience, the Bird Friendliness Index or "BFI"

objectives.description: Significantly increase and stabilize population numbers of grassland birds

partners.tagLine: Our work is co-developed and often led by partner organizations and stakeholders
partners.title: Audubon works with domestic and international partners to promote sustainable ranching and expand and coordinate grassland bird conservation work across Canada, the US and Mexico
partners.description: The infographic on the right outlines the collaborative roles of Audubon staff, ranchers enrolled in the program, and retail partners in the implementation of the Conservation Ranching Program.

objectives.description: Continue collaborating with Bird Studies Canada, Nature Canada and Pronatura Noreste to expand and coordinate conservation ranching tri-nationally.
